  <!-- ═══ WHAT IS CAST STONE ═══ -->
  <section class="csf-section csf-section--alt">
    <div class="container csf-two-col">
      <div class="csf-two-col__text">
        <p class="csf-section__label">The Material</p>
        <h2>What Is a Cast Stone Fireplace?</h2>
        <p>Cast stone is a refined architectural material made from carefully proportioned blends of natural aggregates, white cement, and mineral pigments. The result is a material that looks and feels like hand-carved limestone — with the weight of solid natural stone, the consistency of controlled manufacturing, and a beauty that only deepens with age.</p>
        <p>A cast stone fireplace is a fireplace surround, mantel, or full chimney piece crafted from this material. Unlike prefabricated veneers or hollow foam mantels, a genuine cast stone fireplace is solid, dense, and built to last. It holds up to Texas heat and decades of use without fading, cracking, or looking tired.</p>
        <p>The difference between a cast stone fireplace and a natural stone fireplace is largely one of flexibility and consistency. Natural stone introduces beautiful variation but limits design control. Cast stone gives you the same warmth and weight, while allowing exact proportions, custom profiles, and intricate carving details that would be prohibitively expensive or impossible to achieve with cut stone alone. Learn more in our guide to <a href="/blog/cast-stone-vs-natural-stone">cast stone vs. natural stone</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="csf-two-col__stats">
        <div class="csf-stat">
          <div class="csf-stat__number">20+</div>
          <div class="csf-stat__label">Years serving DFW</div>
        </div>
        <div class="csf-stat">
          <div class="csf-stat__number">500+</div>
          <div class="csf-stat__label">Completed projects</div>
        </div>
        <div class="csf-stat">
          <div class="csf-stat__number">100%</div>
          <div class="csf-stat__label">Custom designed</div>
        </div>
        <div class="csf-stat">
