  <!-- ═══ STYLES ═══ -->
  <section class="csf-section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="csf-section__label">Design Styles</p>
      <h2>Cast Stone Fireplace Styles</h2>
      <p class="csf-section__intro">Cast stone is one of the most versatile architectural materials available, working equally well across a wide range of design languages. Here are the styles our DFW clients most frequently request:</p>
      <div class="csf-styles">
        <div class="csf-style">
          <div class="csf-style__num">01</div>
          <h3>Traditional &amp; Classic</h3>
          <p>Carved details, fluted pilasters, dentil molding, and a full classical surround. These fireplaces draw from Georgian, Federal, and French country architecture and bring a sense of heritage to any room. They're the most requested style in older Highland Park and University Park homes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="csf-style">
          <div class="csf-style__num">02</div>
          <h3>Transitional</h3>
          <p>Clean lines with restrained detail. A transitional cast stone fireplace works in spaces that want a bit of formality without the full weight of traditional ornamentation — perfect for the majority of DFW new construction and remodel projects.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="csf-style">
          <div class="csf-style__num">03</div>
          <h3>Contemporary &amp; Modern</h3>
          <p>Slab faces, linear proportions, no applied ornamentation. Modern cast stone fireplaces are often monolithic — a single bold architectural element in a clean room. We've installed striking contemporary fireplaces in <a href="/service-areas/southlake">Westlake</a>, <a href="/service-areas/southlake">Southlake</a>, and Preston Hollow homes that look like custom millwork but carry the tactile warmth of real stone.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="csf-style">
          <div class="csf-style__num">04</div>
          <h3>Rustic &amp; Farmhouse</h3>
          <p>Rough-hewn textures, chunky proportions, and a warm, unpretentious character. These fireplaces complement exposed wood beams, wide-plank floors, and open living spaces — a popular request for <a href="/service-areas/colleyville">Colleyville</a>, <a href="/service-areas/keller">Keller</a>, and <a href="/service-areas/flower-mound">Flower Mound</a> homes with farmhouse or transitional-country aesthetics.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ PROCESS ═══ -->
