  <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
  <section class="csf-section csf-section--alt">
    <div class="container csf-faq-wrap">
      <div class="csf-faq__head">
        <p class="csf-section__label">FAQs</p>
        <h2>Cast Stone Fireplace FAQs</h2>
        <p>Have a question we didn't answer? <a href="/contact">Contact us</a> — we're happy to help.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="csf-faq__list">
        <details class="csf-faq">
          <summary>How much does a cast stone fireplace cost?</summary>
          <p>Cast stone fireplaces from CAST Design range from approximately $3,500 for a simpler mantel-only installation to $15,000 or more for a full custom surround with hearth and complex carving detail. The cost depends on the size, the complexity of the design, and whether you're doing a new installation or a firebox replacement. We provide a fixed-price quote after the free in-home consultation — no hidden fees, no surprises.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="csf-faq">
          <summary>Is cast stone heat-resistant?</summary>
          <p>Yes. Cast stone is a cement-based material and is naturally heat-tolerant. It will not warp, melt, or degrade with normal fireplace use. Our cast stone mix is specifically engineered to handle the thermal cycling of regular fireplace operation across decades.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="csf-faq">
          <summary>How does cast stone compare to natural stone for a fireplace?</summary>
          <p>Natural stone fireplaces are beautiful but come with trade-offs: high cost, limited design control, and the inconsistency inherent to quarried material. Cast stone delivers the same visual warmth and physical weight at a lower cost, with precise design control and consistent quality. For custom fireplace design, we believe cast stone is actually the superior material for most applications.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="csf-faq">
          <summary>Can a cast stone fireplace be installed on an existing firebox?</summary>
          <p>Absolutely. This is the most common scenario — a homeowner has an existing gas or wood-burning firebox and wants to upgrade from a dated or builder-grade surround to a proper cast stone mantel and surround. We work around your existing firebox dimensions, and our team handles all the installation logistics.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="csf-faq">
          <summary>What fireplace styles are available in cast stone?</summary>
          <p>Cast stone is one of the most design-flexible fireplace materials available. We produce traditional, transitional, contemporary, modern, rustic, and custom architectural styles. If you can describe it or show us a reference image, we can usually build it.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="csf-faq">
          <summary>Do you serve areas outside of Dallas?</summary>
          <p>Yes. We serve the entire Dallas–Fort Worth metroplex, including <a href="/service-areas/fort-worth">Fort Worth</a>, <a href="/service-areas/plano">Plano</a>, <a href="/service-areas/southlake">Southlake</a>, <a href="/service-areas/mckinney">McKinney</a>, <a href="/service-areas/frisco">Frisco</a>, <a href="/service-areas/colleyville">Colleyville</a>, Westlake, <a href="/service-areas/flower-mound">Flower Mound</a>, <a href="/service-areas/keller">Keller</a>, and all surrounding communities. <a href="/service-areas">View all service areas</a>.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

